  "texts": [
    "Additionally, PCA and linear discriminant analysis (LDA) (Wang et al. 2024) remain popular for reducing the dimensionality of sensor arrays while preserving key variance in the data, which enhances interpretability and mitigates overfitting in downstream classifiers.",
    "However, traditional methods are increasingly being augmented or replaced by deep learning techniques that demonstrate superior performance in managing high-dimensional and heterogeneous olfactory data.",
    "Deep learning has transformed the field by enabling the automatic learning of hierarchical features directly from raw sensor data, thereby revealing complex patterns that may remain undetected through manual feature extraction (Ahmed et al. 2023).",
    "Significant advancements in deep learning, particularly in developing models for Bayesian state estimation in high-dimensional spaces, have profound implications for the analysis of olfactory and gustatory signals.",
    "Research involving hierarchical models and neural networks provides effective frameworks for representing complex perceptual data (Hinton and Salakhutdinov 2006)."
  ],
